@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = 
@tenantId = 

### Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Auth — login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "owner@example.com", "password": "your-password" }

### IAM — me
GET {{baseUrl}}/iam/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Businesses
GET {{baseUrl}}/businesses
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Businesses — dashboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/businesses/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Bookings
GET {{baseUrl}}/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}

### Arena meta
GET {{baseUrl}}/arena

### Canteen (location stock)
GET {{baseUrl}}/canteen?locationId=
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}

### Expenses
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses?locationId=
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}

### Assets / inventory (same routes)
GET {{baseUrl}}/assets?locationId=
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}

### Full API surface
# Dashboard / admin: velay-api.postman_collection.json + velay-api.md (repo root)
# Vendor mobile: velay-mobile-api.postman_collection.json
# Legacy full export: booking-saas-all-endpoints.postman_collection.json (repo root)
